  <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>Long gone are the days when snowboarding played second-fiddle to the skiers on the mountain! <br /><br />As snowboarders ourselves, Inghams know how important it is to ensure that you’re visiting the very best resorts and staying in the very best locations and we know that what may be a perfect fit for skis, is not always that way on a snowboard. However with 89 resorts to choose from across 8 countries in Europe and Canada, we’ve got plenty of choice for you to secure your ideal snowboarding holiday this winter! <br /><br />For a helping hand, we’ve put together some of our favourite resorts for the snowboarder in all of us: <br /><br /></p>
<h2>Beginners</h2>
<p>All too often, beginners seek out the most gentle of slopes but what all snowboarders quickly learn, is that what may be considered a nice, kind gradient, more often than not ends in a lengthy flat piste which is all but snowboarder friendly! To avoid that pesky situation, here are some of our favourite resorts to really get the most out of your first week on a board: <br /><br />1. <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/france/alpe-dhuez">Alpe d’Huez, France</a> 2. <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/austria/ski-welt-ski-area/soll">Söll, Austria</a> 3. <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/austria/saalbach-hinterglemm-fieberbrunn-ski-circus/saalbach">Saalbach, Austria</a> 4. <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/italy/the-dolomites-ski-area/kronplatz">Kronplatz, Italy</a> <br /><br /></p>
<h2>Snowparks</h2>
<p>Whether you’re working up to an ollie, you’ve mastered the 540 rodeo flip or you just fancy sitting on the sidelines to watch it all happen, the snowpark is a must-visit once you’ve made it to the mountains. These are some of our favourites: <br /><br />1. <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/france/les-deux-alpes">Les Deux Alpes, France</a> 2. <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/france/espace-killy-ski-area/tignes">Tignes, France</a> 3. <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/france/portes-du-soleil-ski-area">Avoriaz/Morzine, France</a> 4. <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/austria/mayrhofen">Mayrhofen, Austria</a> 5. <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/austria/kitzbuehel-alps/kitzbuhel">Kitzbuhel, Austria</a> 6. <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/italy/milky-way-ski-area/sauze-doulx">Sauze d’Oulx, Italy</a> <br /><br /></p>
<h2>Advanced</h2>
<p>For more advanced snowboarders, the mountains really are your playground and well, no one wants a small playground do they?! With that in mind, we’ve selected some of our favourite resorts to give you access to a fantastic array of terrain to really get the most out of your week: <br /><br />1. <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/austria/arlberg-ski-area/st-anton">St Anton, Austria</a> 2. <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/italy/cervinia">Cervinia, Italy</a> 3. <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/switzerland/zermatt">Zermatt, Switzerland</a> 4. <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/switzerland/verbier">Verbier, Switzerland</a> <br /><br />But if you’re not sure where to snowboard this year, get in touch on <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.facebook.com/inghamsSki/" target="_blank">Facebook</a> or <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://twitter.com/InghamsSki" target="_blank">Twitter</a> or give us a call on 01483 345 657; many of our reservations and product team are seasoned snowboarders and would be happy to find the right resort for you! <br /><br /></p>
